<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,335,722]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Comment: A former 
<typeStatus box="[448,498,496,522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
designation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peters, W. C. H." box="[687,905,496,522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="361 - 369" refId="ref47104" refString="Peters, W. C. H. (1868) Uber die zu den Glossophagae gehorigen Flederthiere und uber eine neue Art der Gattung Coleura. Monatsberichte der Koniglich Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin, 1868, 361 - 369." type="journal article" year="1868">Peters (1868: 870)</bibRefCitation>
was refuted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen, K." box="[1095,1357,496,522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref43224" refString="Andersen, K. (1912) Catalogue of the Chiroptera in the collection of the British Museum. I. Megachiroptera. British Museum (Natural History), London, 854 pp." type="book" year="1912">Andersen (1912: 558)</bibRefCitation>
. However, his rejection, which was based merely on technical grounds, is unjustified as shown by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergmans, W." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="89 - 153" refId="ref43910" refString="Bergmans, W. (1989) Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). The genera Micropteropus Matschie, 1899, Epomops Gray, 1870, Hypsignathus H. Allen, 1861, Nanonycteris Matschie, 1899, and Plerotes Andersen, 1910. Beaufortia, 39 (4), 89 - 153." type="journal article" year="1989">Bergmans (1989: 99)</bibRefCitation>
, and confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kock, D. &amp; Barnett, L. &amp; Fahr, J." box="[421,686,576,602]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="77 - 97" refId="ref45921" refString="Kock, D., Barnett, L., Fahr, J. &amp; Emms, D. (2002) On a collection of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from the Gambia. Acta Chiropterologica, 4 (1), 77 - 97, Warzcaw." type="journal article" year="2002">
Kock 
<emphasis box="[492,552,576,601]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(2002: 82)
</bibRefCitation>
. A further specimen ZMB 
<quantity box="[1006,1095,576,602]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8265" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="3475.0">3475 in</quantity>
the general catalogue is also marked with a 
<typeStatus box="[330,380,616,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
asterisk, presumably by Peters. However, ZMB 3475, which was collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[1313,1384,616,642]" country="Nigeria" name="Lagos" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Lagos</collectingRegion>
and acquired from Salmin, was not part of the original description, hence its marking as “ 
<typeStatus box="[1144,1199,656,682]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
” is rather inexplicable.
</paragraph>
